news.title: Bill to vest nazul property back with Uttar Pradesh government after lease ends cleared
news.para: The Bill was tabled by parliamentary affairs minister Suresh Khanna on behalf of CM. It replaces the ordinance promulgated in March this year with the same purpose.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh housing board hikes circle rates for plots in two townships in Ghaziabad
news.para: Circle rates for the two townships were increased by over 3% in the previous fiscal year even before commercial runs on the corridor began in Oct 2023. Currently, nearly 50% of the 82km corridor is operational.

news.title: YEIDA set to offer 19 plots for group housing near Noida airport
news.para: The plots will be allotted through an e-auction, with reserve prices set between Rs 32,375 and Rs 35,612 per sqm. This scheme is expected to generate at least 25,000 flats, catering to various segments from affordable to luxury housing, officials said.

news.title: MahaRERA orders builders to specify date of delivery of amenities
news.para: The developer will have to include details stating whether the facilities and amenities will be provided in the building, in the common areas, or in the layout, including even the type of lifts.

news.title: Deloitte leases 1.75 lakh sq ft office space at Prestige Trade Tower in Delhi
news.para: This is the Bengaluru-headquartered Prestige Group’s first commercial project in Delhi. It had entered into a joint venture with DB Realty in 2019 to develop a hospitality-led mixed use project spread over 7.7 acres of land in Delhi’s Aerocity.

news.title: Action Construction Equipment's profit grows 24% to Rs 84.57 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: "The company has maintained its growth momentum in the first quarter of the current fiscal year. The company has been able to deliver its best ever quarterly performance in Q1 FY25," Action Construction Equipment Executive Director Sorab Agarwal said.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's net profit declines 15.28% in Q1 FY25
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,576.96 crore in Q1 FY25, a dip of 9.44 per cent from Rs 1,741.38 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Prestige Estates Projects' net profit dips 3.40% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,024.50 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 2.96 per cent from Rs 1,966.30 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: SC asks Bombay HC to conduct performance audit of 1971 Maharashtra law on slum development
news.para: ​The top court asked the chief justice of the high court to set up a bench to "initiate suo motu proceedings" to review the working of the Maharashtra Slum Areas (Improvement, Clearance and Redevelopment) Act, 1971 to identify the problems faced in its implementation.

news.title: Hong Kong court adjourns Shimao Group's liquidation petition until August 12
news.para: Many Chinese property developers are facing liquidation lawsuits by creditors since the sector slipped into a debt crisis in 2021, with a handful, such as industry giant China Evergrande Group, ordered to be liquidated.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas' net profit dips 80.36% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,641 crore in Q1 FY25, a dip of 6.18 per cent from Rs 2,814.98 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Puravankara posts Rs 14.78 crore profit in Q1 FY25
news.para: Puravankara's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 675.55 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 101.17 per cent from Rs 335.81 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: China's Zhengzhou city allows developers to sell new homes at reduced prices
news.para: "The housing regulator no longer guides the sales price of new homes, and developers set their own prices for sales," the regulator's notice said.

news.title: Asahi India Glass' net profit declines 25.39% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Asahi India Glass' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,135.83 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 4.14 per cent from Rs 1,090.69 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: CapitaLand India Trust Management reports 21% growth in net property income for H1 2024
news.para: Total property income and net property income for the period grew by 23% and 21% y-o-y to S$136.1 million and S$103.5 million for H1 2024, respectively.

news.title: Ambuja Cements posts profit of Rs 789.63 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Ambuja Cements' revenue from operations was at Rs 8,311.48 crore during the June quarter compared to Rs 8,712.90 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal.

news.title: Omaxe may challenge Sebi order barring company, chairman, MD from securities market
news.para: ​The Sebi order had a negative impact on Omaxe's share prices. The stock of the company on Wednesday declined 4.99 per cent to Rs 152.20 apiece -- its lower circuit limit -- on the BSE.

news.title: Godrej Properties' profit jumps over four-fold to Rs 520 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: The total income grew to Rs 1,699.48 crore during April-June period of 2024-25 fiscal from Rs 1,265.98 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: House is a house, can't be an asset: Revenue secretary on indexation benefits
news.para: Revenue Secretary, Ministry of Finance clarified that the rollover benefits will continue on capital gains of up to Rs 10 crore under the new structure.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces' net profit drops 44% to Rs 5 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces bookings for the quarter grew 49% to Rs 201 crore, while collections stood at Rs 248 crore, up 21% from a year ago, the company said in a release.
